<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF80CE50FCD5FB2BDF1D3A1B" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF80CE50FCD5FB2BDE4539C2" blockId="13.[810,1452,1274,1589]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF80CE50FCD5FB2BD8F7393A" bold="true" box="[810,932,1274,1300]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF80CE50FBBAFB2BDFCA393A" box="[1093,1177,1274,1300]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF80CE50FBBAFB2BDFCA393A" box="[1093,1177,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">tarsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the following combination of characters: medium total length; legs and palps without coloration patterns; bulb with three keels; serrated area distal to PAc in prolateral view of copulatory bulb absent or small; BTA absent; embolus inserted in a right angle; embolar apex flattened and expanded, arrow-shaped in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF80CE50FCA0FA27DF1D3A1B" blockId="13.[810,1452,1274,1589]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF80CE50FCA0FA27DF623A3E" bold="true" box="[863,1073,1526,1552]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF80CE50FBC0FA26DEF43A3F" authority="Perty, 1833" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[1087,1447,1526,1553]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF80CE50FBC0FA26DE433A3E" box="[1087,1296,1526,1553]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Actinopus tarsalis</emphasis>
